Each note has this tuple in it.

00:48:27.825 --> 00:48:29.495
AUDIENCE: Then i is the note.

00:48:29.495 --> 00:48:30.120
PROFESSOR: Yep.

00:48:30.120 --> 00:48:32.028
AUDIENCE: So i
connects to i plus 1.

00:48:32.028 --> 00:48:34.097
And then all
possibilities known.

00:48:34.097 --> 00:48:34.680
PROFESSOR: OK.

00:48:34.680 --> 00:48:36.610
So this connects to i plus 1.

00:48:36.610 --> 00:48:40.880
And then all possible
destinations, right?

00:48:40.880 --> 00:48:44.380
So I'm going to say left.

00:48:44.380 --> 00:48:45.360
This is after the jump.

00:48:45.360 --> 00:48:48.630
So, left after the jump,
and right after the jump.

00:48:48.630 --> 00:48:54.340
And this is for all
possible left after a jump,

00:48:54.340 --> 00:48:55.710
right after the jump.

00:48:55.710 --> 00:49:02.780
